<section id="two-html-files" class="wrapper-content bg-white">
	<h2>Working with your two HTML files</h2>
	<p>You will begin by working with two HTML files: </p>
	<ul>
		<li>The template file you will <i>copy from</i> and</li>
		<li>The web page you will <i>copy to</i>.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Start Visual Studio Code.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>From your <b>websites\templates</b> folder, open <i>one</i> of the following two HTML files. You can choose whichever footer version you like better.
		<div class="four-samples">
			<div>
				<img src="../assets/img/project-smoothies-footer/pic-footer-template-1.png" alt="Sample image" style="margin-bottom: 8px">
				<a href="../../templates/footer-template.html" target="_blank" style="display: inline-block">footer-template.html</a>
			</div>
			<div>
				<img src="../assets/img/project-smoothies-footer/pic-footer-template-2.png" alt="Sample image"  style="margin-bottom: 8px">
				<a href="../../templates/footer-template-2.html" target="_blank" style="display: inline-block">footer-template-2.html</a>
			</div>
		</div></li>
		<li>From your <b>websites\portfolio\software</b> folder, open your web page named <b>index.html</b>.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/file-explorer-html.png" alt="fa-icons-copy">
		If you have any other files open in Visual Studio, you may wish to close them.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/vscode-files-open-html.png" alt="fa-icons-copy">
		This will help you to focus <em>only</em> on the two HTML files you will be working with.</li>
	</ol>


	
	<h3 id="copy-footer-html">Copying-and-pasting the footer HTML</h3>

	<p>Your next step is to copy content from the HTML template file into your <b>index.html</b> web page.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>In the footer template file, select and copy the footer.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/vscode-footer-copy-html.png" alt="fa-icons-copy"></li>
		<li>In your <b>index.html</b> web page, scroll down to near the end of the web page, to just before the closing <b>&lt;/body&gt;</b> tag.</li>
		<li>Press the <b>ENTER</b> key a few times to open up some new lines of blank space, and paste the copied footer content.</li>
		<li>When finished, save your <b>index.html</b> web page.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>You can now close both the footer template file and your saved <b>index.html</b> web page.</p>

</section>


<section id="two-css-files" class="wrapper-content bg-white">
	<h2>Working with your two CSS files</h2>
	<p>Your next task is to work with two CSS files: </p>
	<ul>
		<li>The template CSS file you will <i>copy from</i> and</li>
		<li>The stylesheet you will <i>copy to</i>.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>In Visual Studio Code:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>From your <b>websites\templates</b> folder, open <i>one</i> of the following two CSS files. Choose whichever one is for the footer template file you choose earlier.
		<ul>
			<li><b>footer-template.css</b></li>
		</ul>
		-or-
		<ul>
			<li><b>footer-template-2.css</b></li>
		</ul></li>
		<li>From your <b>websites\portfolio\software\assets\css</b> folder, open your stylesheet named <b>style.css</b>.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/file-explorer-css.png" alt="fa-icons-copy">
		If you have any other files open in Visual Studio, you may wish to close them.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/vscode-files-open-css.png" alt="fa-icons-copy">
		This will help you to focus <em>only</em> on the two CSS files you will be working with.</li>
	</ol>



	<h3 id="copy-footer-css">Copying-and-pasting the footer CSS</h3>

	<p>Your next step is to copy content from the footer template CSS file into your <b>style.css</b> web page.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>In your footer template CSS file, select and copy the footer.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-smoothies-footer/vscode-footer-copy-css.png" alt="fa-icons-copy"></li>
		<li>Switch to your <b>style.css</b> file, and, at the bottom, paste the copied footer styles.</li>
		<li>When finished, save your <b>style.css</b> stylesheet.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>You can now close both the template footer CSS file and your saved <b>style.css</b> stylesheet.</p>
</section>


<section id="footer-hyperlinks" class="wrapper-content bg-white">
	<h2>Editing the footer hyperlinks</h2>

	<p>Your next step is to edit the pasted content in your <b>index.html</b> file.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>In VS Code, open your <b>index.html</b> web page and scroll down to the footer.</li>
		<li>As required, edit or remove the email address and social media hyperlinks in the footer that are copied from the template file.</li>
		<li>Edit the hyperlinks to the three other web pages on your personal website as shown below.</li>
		<ul>
		<ul>
		<li>Edit the link to your website <b>Home page</b> as follows:
<pre class="language-html">
  &lt;<span class="blue-dark">a</span> <span class="blue-light">href</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"../../index.html"</span>&gt;<span class="white">Home</span>&lt;/<span class="blue-dark">a</span>&gt;
</pre></li>

<li>Edit the link to your website <b>Portfolio page</b> as follows:
<pre class="language-html">
  &lt;<span class="blue-dark">a</span> <span class="blue-light">href</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"../index.html"</span>&gt;<span class="white">Portfolio</span>&lt;/<span class="blue-dark">a</span>&gt;
</pre></li>

<li>Edit the link to your website <b>Privacy page</b> as follows:
<pre class="language-html">
  &lt;<span class="blue-dark">a</span> <span class="blue-light">href</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"../../privacy.html"</span>&gt;<span class="white">Privacy</span>&lt;/<span class="blue-dark">a</span>&gt;
</pre>

	If you have choosen the <b>footer-template-2.html</b>, edit the privacy link as follows:
<pre class="language-html">
  &lt;<span class="blue-dark">a</span> <span class="blue-light">class</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"privacy-legal"</span> <span class="blue-light">href</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"../../privacy.html"</span>&gt;<span class="white">Privacy & Legal</span>&lt;/<span class="blue-dark">a</span>&gt;
</pre></li>

<li>And if your footer has a link to your website <b>Contact Form</b> page, edit it as follows:
<pre class="language-html">
  &lt;<span class="blue-dark">a</span> <span class="blue-light">href</span><span class="white">=</span><span class="brown">"../../contact/index.html"</span>&gt;<span class="white">Contact</span>&lt;/<span class="blue-dark">a</span>&gt;
</pre></li>
</ol>

	<p>You are now finished working with this HTML file and can close it in Visual Studio Code.</p>


	<h3 id="footer-background">Editing the footer background colour</h3>
	<p>You need to change the background colour of your footer so that it matches the rest of your project web page.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>In VS Code, open your <b>style.css</b> stylesheet.</li>
		<li>Scroll down to the <b>.container-footer</b> selector. This contains the value for the footer <b>background-color</b>.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/vscode-bg-colour.png" alt="fa-icons-copy"></li>
		<li>Change the value from the dark grey of <b>#2c3e50</b> to the green of <b>#5ba745</b>.
		<span class="inside-ol">&nbsp;</span>
		If you have chosen the <b>footer-template-2.html</b> and <b>footer-template-2.css</b> template files, you will want to change the colour of the <b>.container-footer h5</b> text from grey (<b>#8d9093</b>) to white (<b>#fff</b>).
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/vscode-footer-fonts-h5.png" alt="fa-icons-copy"></li>
		<li>When finished, save your <b>style.css</b> stylesheet.</li>
	</ol>
	
	<p>You have now completed this Tutorial.</p>

	<p>You can display a <a href="../final/final-software-footer/after/one/index.html" target="_blank" title="Web Design Project: Software Analytics 2n2l.com Brendan Munnelly">finished version</a> of this project web page by clicking the image below.</p>
	<p><a href="../final/final-software-footer/after/one/index.html" class="img-link" target="_blank"><img SRC="../assets/img/project-software-footer/software-finished.png" alt="Web Design Project: Software Analytics 2n2l.com Brendan Munnelly"></a></p>

	<p>You can view the alternative version with the centred footer <a href="../final/final-software-footer/after/two/index.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>


	<p>In later a Tutorial for this portfolio project you will add <a href="../project-software-menus/index.html">desktop/laptop and mobile menus</a>.</p>

</section>




<section id="publish-github" class="wrapper-content">

	<h2>Uploading your project to GitHub</h2>
	<p>The final step is to upload your project to GitHub.</p>
	<p>All the files you have updated for this project are in the <b>software</b> sub-folder of your <b>websites/portfolio</b> folder.</p>
	
	<p>So the easiest option is simply to upload the <i>entire</i> <b>software</b> sub-folder to your account on GitHub.</p>

	<ol>
		<li>If you are not already signed in to your GitHub account, sign in now.</li>

		<li>On the left of your GitHub home page, click the name of the repository that holds your web pages.</li>
		
		<li>On the next GitHub screen displayed, click the <b>portfolio</b> folder.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/github-portfolio.png" alt="GitHub Upload"></li>

		<li>GitHub should now display your <b>portfolio</b> folder.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/github-upload-portfolio.png" alt="github-upload-portfolio"></li>

		<li>With the <b>portfolio</b> folder displayed on your GitHub screen, click the <b>Add file</b> button and, from the dropdown list displayed, choose the option <b>Upload files</b>.

		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/github-btn-add-file-dropdown.png" alt="Project Animation Google Fonts"></li>

		<li>In File/Windows Explorer on your computer, display your <b>portfolio</b> folder and then drag-and-drop the <b>software</b> folder to the GitHub tab in your web browser.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/github-upload-drag-drop.png" alt="github-upload-drag-drop"></li>

		<li>After uploading the <b>software</b> folder, scroll down to the bottom of the GitHub screen, enter a short message in the <b>Commit changes</b> box, click the <b>Commit changes</b> button, and wait for the upload to complete.
		<img src="../assets/img/project-software-footer/github-upload-progress.png" alt="github-upload-progress"></li>

	</ol>

	<p>Your updated &#8216;Software Analytics&#8217; project web page is now published on GitHub at a web address similar to the following, where <b>username</b> is the username you have chosen for your GitHub account:</p>
	
	<p><b>https://username.github.io/portfolio/software/index.html</b></p>
	<p>or, simply:</p>
	<p><b>https://username.github.io/portfolio/software</b></p>

	<p>It may take a few minutes for your uploaded files to appear on GitHub.</p>

	<p><br><br>Return to <a href="../../index.html">Contents</a>.</p>

